OL,6,FManchester Minshull Street Crown Court
OL,7,Fheard she was suffering with "abnormal
OL,8,Fmental functioning" at the time of the
OL,9,Foffence with witnesses describing how
OL,10,Fthey thought she was "having a mental
OL,11,Fbreakdown".
OL,13,FThe court heard she was earlier at a
OL,14,Fsupported living facility before being
OL,15,Ftaken to Judy's house.
OL,17,FMark Rhind KC, prosecuting, said: "The
OL,18,Ffactual background is that the
OL,19,Fdefendant was suffering some kind of
OL,20,Fmental crisis at the time of this
OL,21,Fincident.
