OL,3,CWoman admits manslaughter of her
OL,4,Cgrandmother
OL,6,F"She was at Vernon House and staff
OL,7,Fthere described her as being agitated,
OL,8,Fabusive, making threats and they
OL,9,Ffeeling both frightened and
OL,10,Ffrightening.
OL,12,F"Witnesses thought she was having a
OL,13,Fmental breakdown. Three expert reports
OL,14,Fdescribe that the staff at Vernon
OL,15,FHouse did not feel safe with her there.
OL,17,F"The police were in a catch-22
OL,18,Fsituation - she hadn't committed any
OL,19,Foffences but she couldn't stay there."
